This paper is about a neural network-based approach for anomaly detection, which falls under the category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on backpropagation neural networks and their application to semi-supervised anomaly detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the optimization of the proposed approach for on-device learning, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
